<br>
First of all, here is the goal: <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Leather Padding</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  Tailoring Trivial of 31, which is extremely easy to get.  You will want your tailoring at 60+ to reduce the number of failed combines.  See the bottom of this guide for details on how to raise it.  Leather padding requires 2 components - 1 silk thread or shade silk thread, and 1 Low Quality wolf/cat/bear/rockhopper hide.  The silk thread is a no-fail subcombine of 2 spiderling or shadeling silks (NOT spider). *note - Shadeling silk only works with LQ Rockhopper Hides.<br>
<br>
With me so far?  So your goal is to get spiderling or shadeling silk, and LQ hides.  First Stop: Everfrost Peaks.<br>
<br>
Take the PoK book to Halas.  It will park you in one of 2 perfect spots to farm spiderling silk.   First, run to the two merchants outside Halas (unless they don't like you) and see if they have any silks or hides for sale.  Buying 100 of them for 5 silver each is a GREAT thing!  Then, summon a pet (Monster Summoning is fun here.  Recast til you get an ice giant), and let it do all the work.  Kill everything with more than 2 legs.  If your tailoring is below 20, keep all the ruined pelts and see basic tailoring 101 at the bottom.  Otherwise, only loot LQ/MQ/HQ pelts and destroy the rest.  Concentrate on the spiderling silks, and move around the canyons to get more.  In 1 hour, you should have the 3 stacks of silk you need, and maybe 3 LQ hides.<br>
<br>
Now book it to Marus Seru.  Bring SoW potions or make friends with the local shamans.  Your new target: Greyhoppers - lvl 24-26.  They drop LQ hides like rain, and the remaining Greyhopper Hides are great for getting tailoring above 60.<br>
<br>
Marus is a bit dangerous at 24-34.  There are 2 mobs that aggro - Lightcrawlers (nasty giant centipedes - faster than SoW!) and Zelniaks (nasty mutant camels with a HUGE aggro radius).  Neither has good loot, so avoid unless you really just like killing them.  Pick a wide open spot with good visibility, and park your armored and armed fire pet.  Use a low level nuke, and pull greyhoppers to the pet.  Lower levels should stick to single pulls.  After 34, pulling 3 or more is safe w/o adds.  39+ you can take 6+.  I use burn to pull, then drag the doomed creature right by my pet, then I use a switch key where the pet backs off his target and attacks mine.  Run out and grab another, heal if necessary.  Once he gets 4 or 5 on him, I often throw in a rain to speed up the kills.  After 1 hour, you should have about 2 stacks of LQ hides and 1 stack of greyhopper hides.  Time to do some tailoring!  Head to PoK, Nexus, or your favorite safe zone of choice.<br>
<br>
Combine 2 silks (NOT stacked!) to get a silk thread, then 1 silk thread and 1 LQ hide for each padding.  When you have exhausted your supply of resources, head to bazaar with at least 1 stack of padding.<br>
<br>
Set up shop, check the price, and /auction your leather padding.  I've seen them as low as 20pp ea, and as high as 50pp ea.  I sell them for 20 or 25, which is 400 or 500pp for the stack.  In the 2 months I've been making and selling LP, I have yet to wait 10 minutes from the first auction call to the sale, YMMV.  <br>
<br>
Repeat til rich.  The more you do it, the faster it will go.  If you get impatient (like I often do), you can /auction in either zone to buy the components.  I often buy Spiderling silk in Everfrost from the large population of nekidnoobiebarbs running around. 1-2pp each is fair and won't take a huge chunk out of the profit, but they could get 5pp ea in bazaar.  Also check bazaar prices for silks and threads. 2pp or less for silk and 4pp or less for thread is always a good buy.<br>
<br>
Hope it works for others like it has worked for me.  I am now 2.5k closer to buying my first horse!  <br>
